   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>LIFE-STUDY OF FIRST AND SECOND SAMUEL MESSAGE TWENTY-THREE THE HISTORY CONCERNING DAVID 10 CROWNED BY THE PEOPLE TO BE THE KING</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>FOR THE KINGDOM OF GOD ON THE EARTH</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>2 SAMUEL 2 24 4 DAVID'S CARE FOR GOD'S HABITATION ON THE EARTH 2 Scripture Reading: 2 Sam 7</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>In the foregoing message we saw from chapter six that David took care of the habitation of the ark.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>In this message we will see that, according to chapter seven, David wanted to build a house for God.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Concerning this matter I have a very particular burden.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>II.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>WANTING TO BUILD A HOUSE FOR GOD A. Considering That He Himself</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Dwelled in a House of Cedar,</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>but That the Ark of God</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>Dwelled within Curtains</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>David considered that he himself dwelled in a house of cedar but that the ark of God dwelled within curtains v. 2b .</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>B. Releasing His Consideration</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>to Nathan the Prophet</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>David released his consideration to Nathan the prophet, who encouraged him to go and do what was in his heart, telling David that Jehovah was with him vv.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>2a, 3 .</S>
   </TEXT>
